"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-comment-paris-olympic-games-2024-opening-ceremony-b1173095.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Comment  Get our award-winning daily news email featuring exclusive stories, opinion and expert analysis    I would like to be emailed about offers, event and updates from Evening Standard.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourprivacy notice.\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From the audacious opening ceremony - the first to take place outside of a stadium - to the allegedly \\\"anti-sex\\\" beds in the Olympic village, Paris 2024 is doing things a little bit differently.\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 586, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.053953871241181e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The news this morning of amassive arson attack which has brought chaos to France's rail network servesas a reminder of the security undertaking involved.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 714, \"end\": 720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9280639677279554, \"rank\": 0.04183491879499408, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And no doubt, there are misgivings from some Parisians, as indeed there were among Londoners in the build-up to 2012.\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But with a fair wind, those are likely to melt away as even the most curmudgeonly of locals are caught up in the Olympic magic.\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 1040, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games have also been good news for London.\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1081, \"end\": 1087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999997632908235, \"rank\": 2.364989274570159e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The capital is no one's second prize, but our city has become the official overspill venue, with occupancy at top end hotels pretty much at capacity, and the Eurostar enjoying a roaring trade.\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1247, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.999999996344286, \"rank\": 3.655548055162377e-09, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We wish all Team GB athletes bonne chance.\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1294, \"end\": 1301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9417756718067802, \"rank\": 0.06112914151959979, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even at the best of times, it is said that being leader of the Opposition is the worst job in British politics.\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999917916343668, \"rank\": 4.892301205025282e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And for the Conservative Party, these are far from the best of times.\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1450, \"end\": 1468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 5.034171715931383e-12, \"text\": \"Conservative Party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the general election, the Tories have been reduced to a rump of 121 MPs - but of course, they still need a leader.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"score\": 0.9999999996339284, \"rank\": 3.6608150287110126e-10, \"text\": \"Tories\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would be easy to assume, given the state of Parliament and low esteem the last government was held in by the public, that the Conservatives have a free hit.\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1681, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.99540897372039, \"rank\": 0.002312609908869858, \"text\": \"Parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1763, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\", \"score\": 0.9526378557991465, \"rank\": 0.04022824781603597, \"text\": \"Conservatives\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That the next leader has no chance of becoming prime minister.\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet this would be to ignore the growing volatility of British politics.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1911, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999917916343668, \"rank\": 4.892301205025282e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Labour can go from Jeremy Corbyn to Downing Street in less than five years, there is no reason why the Tories cannot tread a similar path.\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 2070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 0.8775470460639719, \"rank\": 0.13355883814919406, \"text\": \"Labour\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 1951, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Corbyn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeremy Corbyn\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Corbyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Corbyn\"}, {\"begin\": 2035, \"end\": 2041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"score\": 0.9999999996339284, \"rank\": 3.6608150287110126e-10, \"text\": \"Tories\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in order to do so, they will need to elect the right leader.\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And for any chance of that happening, MPs and ordinary members will have to properly analyse why their party lost the election so decisively.\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They will need to make people care about the process - using the summer months to have debates about policy, not simply personality.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We will know more about how likely that will be when the nominations close on Monday.\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Boss is back - though in truth, he never went away.\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2499, \"end\": 2507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Boss_Man\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.232763119605082e-20, \"text\": \"The Boss\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Boss_Man\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Boss_Man\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bruce Springsteenscreamed \\\"no surrender\\\" as the rain began to fall over Wembley Stadiumlast night.\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2627, \"end\": 2634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wembley_Stadium\", \"score\": 0.9999981923863709, \"rank\": 1.1822954616097816e-06, \"text\": \"Wembley\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wembley_Stadium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wembley_Stadium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 74, he is not yet old enough to run for US president, but he more than wowed the crowd and the Standard's Robbie Griffiths, who awarded all five stars while concluding: \\\"In the end, it's just an ordinary night for Bruce and his gang, but one of the best shows most of us have ever seen.\\\"\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2698, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9474547542765485, \"rank\": 0.04012266647612043, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2764, \"end\": 2770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"score\": 0.9996912263647099, \"rank\": 0.0003088396115324154, \"text\": \"Robbie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"